\title{isparkagwise: Agwise Modelling Framework for iSPARK Project}
\description{
The \code{ispark-agwise} package provides a reproducible end-to-end pipeline to generate
fertilizer recommendations for African countries. The pipeline can be implemented
for any country in Africa as it relies on Africa-only data sources (iSDA Soil).
}
\details{
\subsection{Main Features}{
\itemize{
\item \strong{Field-level analysis}: Estimate best linear unbiased predictions (BLUPs) of
field-level response to fertilizer inputs
\item \strong{Environmental covariates}: Integrate soil properties (iSDA), topography (DEM),
and climate (WorldClim) data
\item \strong{Machine learning}: Train predictive models for site-specific fertilizer recommendations
\item \strong{Reproducible pipeline}: Fully documented workflow from raw data to recommendations
}
}

\subsection{Workflow}{

The typical data pipeline consists of:
\enumerate{
\item \strong{Field-level modeling} (\code{blups()}): Analyze yield response to N/P/K fertilizers
\item \strong{Covariate extraction} (\code{covs()}): Download and process environmental data
\item \strong{Data preparation} (\code{data.ml()}): Merge field and environmental data
\item \strong{Machine learning} (\code{ml.execute()}): Train site-specific recommendation models
}
}

\subsection{Data Sources}{
\itemize{
\item \strong{Soil}: iSDA (Innovative Solutions for Decision Agriculture) - 17 soil properties
at two depths (20cm, 50cm)
\item \strong{Topography}: SRTM30 digital elevation model - elevation, slope, TRI, TPI
\item \strong{Climate}: WorldClim - temperature (max, mean) and precipitation
\item \strong{Administrative}: GADM - country and regional boundaries
}
}

